article.description: — Ben Shungu had 23 points as Vermont rolled past Binghamton 74-42 in the semifinals of the America East Conference tournament on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Vermont gets past Binghamton 74-42 in America East tourney
article.linkText: Vermont gets past Binghamton 74-42 in America East tourney
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- — Ben Shungu had 23 points as Vermont rolled past Binghamton 74-42 in the semifinals of the America East Conference tournament on Wednesday night. Ryan Davis had 19 points for Vermont (27-5). Jacob Falko had 13 points for the Bearcats (12-17). Binghamton scored 15 second-half points, a season low for the team. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
